model.filemanagement.decoders

Class RLEDecoder

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.filemanagement.decoders.Decoder
      • model.filemanagement.decoders.RLEDecoder

  • public class RLEDecoder
extends Decoder
    This class handles the interpretation of RLE files. One method reads the meta data and creates the game board and the second method translates the files to our byte[][] game board.
    Version:
    4.0 This class has been the focus of our attention for some time and we developed several versions and this is as of now our final version. Changed the interpretation logic from regex to if-else branching and we used JProfiler to measure performance increase upwards of 4000%!, 5.0 Fixed bug in RLE decoding where position near the edges didn't parse correctly

    • Method Detail

      • decode

        public void decode()
            throws PatternFormatException,
                   java.io.IOException
        "Samlemetode" that controls the flow of the RLE file parsing This method calls other methods in this class with the purpose of doing the following:

        1. Open a file via FileChooser and read the file to a String 2. Read the x and y value from the String and create a board with those values. 3. Read the file meta data(creator, name etc.) and do something with it(Too be implemented) 4. Interpret the RLE String char by char and convert to a board consisting of dead and alive cells(We create an empty board with dead cells and iterate the board and setting alive cells to true according to the RLE file read) Exception

        Specified by:
        decode in class Decoder
        Throws:
        PatternFormatException - Throws an exception if the method is unable to parse the RLE file
        java.io.IOException - If an unspecified I/O error occurs

      • parseMetadata

        private void parseMetadata(java.io.BufferedReader reader)
                    throws PatternFormatException,
                           java.io.IOException
        Reads the metadata from the previously loaded contents and stores it in a new MetaData-object. If the metadata is incorrectly formatted then it will not be stored. This method is not meant to be called directly, but rather through the decode() method in a RLEDecoder-object.
        Parameters:
        reader - The BufferedReader to open
        Throws:
        PatternFormatException - Throws an exception if the method is unable to parse the RLE file
        java.io.IOException - If an unspecified I/O error occurs
        See Also:
        MetaData
